Fix flick-derived toss/spike not being reflected

Root cause (toss): the right-zone gesture fires actionDown on pointerdown
(which locks setPrompt.pressed with the timing) and setChoice only on
release. The sim's setChoice ignored the choice once pressed was set, so
the flicked technique showed a hint but never changed the actual toss.

- sim: allow setChoice to update setPrompt.choice any time before the
  toss resolves (resolveToss reads choice later), not only while unpressed.
- client (spike): route all spike flicks through spikePreset so they
  commit immediately regardless of charge length — U=feint(0.22),
  D=control(0.55), L/R=course smash(power .85 + aim ±0.9). Previously L/R
  used aimSet+actionUp, which gave near-zero power on a quick flick.

Adds scripts/test-flick.ts: drives the sim in the real flick order
(press then setChoice) and asserts the toss technique is reflected.

